+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PhRrg7FogKaWhTbnNTURqR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n     2→\n     3→Add per-queue limits on how many tasks can be processed at the same time.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- Each queue can have a maximum concurrency setting that limits how many tasks can be in a processing state simultaneously.\n     8→- If the concurrency limit is reached, retrieving a task returns `null` even if pending tasks are available.\n     9→- Completing or failing a task frees up a concurrency slot.\n    10→- By default, queues have no concurrency limit (unlimited).\n    11→- There should be a way to set and query the concurrency limit and current active count for a queue.\n    12→- Concurrency interacts correctly with priority ordering -- the highest-priority available task is still chosen, subject to the concurrency limit.\n    13→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018AXXupVqJ6TjwZQRkyLuon","session_id":"d55f7efa-1a7c-4c18-baa6-46556b297090","uuid":"014582e8-7a8d-4559-b9e0-b7e271ede36e"}
